attle-hastings/","urlTitle":"English Heritage - Battle of Hastings","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705183,"age":26,"year":"1086","julianDay":2117714,"title":"Domesday Book","description":"Domesday Book is Britain's earliest extant public record with information containing land surveys and landholdings commissioned by William I. The book was completed in 1086.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/domesday/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Domesday","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705184,"age":36,"year":"1096","julianDay":2121366,"title":"The Crusades","description":"A series of religious wars between Christians and Muslims, known as the Crusades, occurred between 1096 and 1291, and played a large role in European Christian dominance in the Middle East.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/middle-ages/crusades","urlTitle":"History - The Crusades","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Warin Eyton was born in 1060, in Noron-l'Abbaye, Calvados, Normandy, France, his father, Guillaume Pantulf, was 40 and his mother, Béatrice de Normandie, was 34. He married Mrs Warin Eyton before 1097, in Europe. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died after 1097, in Eyton on the Weald Moors, Shropshire, England."},"et":{"1060–after 1097":"1060–pärast 1097","1060–1097":"1060–1097","–Female":"Surnud","1097–1160":"1097–1160","1020–1086":"1020–1086","1026–1052":"1026–1052","1026":"1026","before 1097":"enne 1097","1066":"1066","after 1097":"pärast 1097","1086":"1086","1097":"1097","1020":"1020","1096":"1096","1052":"1052","1160":"1160","1060":"1060","Eyton on the Weald Moors, Shropshire, England":"Eyton on the Weald Moors, Shropshire, England","Noron-L'Abbaye, Calvados, Normandy, France":"Noron-l'Abbaye, Calvados, Normandie, Prantsusmaa","Europe":"Europe","Dover, Kent, England":"Dover, Kent, England"},"fi":{"1060–after 1097":"1060–1097 jälkeen","1060–1097":"1060–1097","–Female":"Kuollut","1097–1160":"1097–1160","1020–1086":"1020–1086","1026–1052":"1026–1052","1026":"1026"